"{\"uid\": \"thesouthafrican.com-sport-paris-olympics-2024-everything-we-know-about-the-paris-olympics-2024-opening-ceremony-date-venue-time\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Copyright Blue Sky Publications (Pty) Ltd. All Rights Reserved.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 63, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 15, \"end\": 18, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_UK\", \"score\": 0.97594630425033, \"rank\": 0.024119468244917504, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_UK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_UK\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"thesouthafrican.com is a division of Blue Sky Publications Ltd. Reproduction without permission prohibited  Home\\u00bbSport\\u00bbParis Olympics 2024\\u00bbEverything we know about the Paris Olympics 2024 opening ceremony  Plans for the opening ceremony at the Paris Olympics 2024 have been a closely guarded secret.\", \"from\": 65, \"to\": 364, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 110, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_UK\", \"score\": 0.97594630425033, \"rank\": 0.024119468244917504, \"text\": \"Sky\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_UK\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sky_UK\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's what we know \\u2026  Plans for theopening ceremonyat theParis Olympics 2024- the first time a Summer Games will start outside a stadium - have been a closely guarded secret.\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 540, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the latest Paris Olympics 2024 news, bookmarkThe South African website'sdedicated section  Here is what we know about theconcept, the artists and music:  Instead of using the main athletics stadium for the opening parade, as is customary, organisers have moved the event outside and into the heart of the capital - in keeping with their motto \\\"Games Wide Open\\\".\", \"from\": 542, \"to\": 907, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Around 6 000-7 000 athletes are set to sail down a six-kilometre stretch of the river Seine from the Austerlitz bridge in the east to the Eiffel Tower, on 85 barges and boats.\", \"from\": 909, \"to\": 1084, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1010, \"end\": 1020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"score\": 0.9996183474668879, \"rank\": 0.00038179824554134066, \"text\": \"Austerlitz\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gare_d'Austerlitz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Up to 500 000 people are set to watch in person from specially built stands, where tickets have sold for up to \\u20ac2 700 (R53 500), on the river banks for free, and from the overlooking balconies and apartments.\", \"from\": 1086, \"to\": 1294, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Organising a ceremony on the Seine is not easier than doing it in a stadium\\u2026 but it has more punch,\\\" chief organiser Tony Estanguet told AFP earlier this month.\", \"from\": 1296, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1326, \"end\": 1331, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9634672690866536e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}, {\"begin\": 1414, \"end\": 1428, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}, {\"begin\": 1434, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.914788629346157e-15, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Because of the size and complexity of the parade, it has never been rehearsed in full.\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The show has been designed by theatre director Thomas Jolly, a 42-year-old prodigy known for hit rock-opera musical \\\"Starmania\\\".\", \"from\": 1547, \"to\": 1675, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1594, \"end\": 1600, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"score\": 0.9844081385706764, \"rank\": 0.010481020285751251, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Tank_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He brought on board a creative team that includes the writer of French TV series \\\"Call My Agent\\\", Fanny Herrero, as well as best-selling author Leila Slimani and renowned historian Patrick Boucheron.\", \"from\": 1677, \"to\": 1876, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1741, \"end\": 1747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9944795295983407, \"rank\": 0.005125731490609682, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3723049673880423e-14, \"text\": \"Fanny\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Fanny_Mendelssohn\"}, {\"begin\": 1821, \"end\": 1826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leila_Roy\", \"score\": 0.9980147968024718, \"rank\": 0.0016821371966256337, \"text\": \"Leila\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leila_Roy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leila_Roy\"}, {\"begin\": 1827, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Slimani\", \"types\": [\"Q937857\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Islam_Slimani\"}, {\"begin\": 1858, \"end\": 1865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"score\": 0.9577884742246815, \"rank\": 0.023307393237596563, \"text\": \"Patrick\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Saint_Patrick\"}, {\"begin\": 1866, \"end\": 1875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boucheron\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The show has been split into 12 different sections, with around 3 000 dancers, singers and entertainers set to be positioned on both banks of the river, the bridges and atop nearby monuments.\", \"from\": 1878, \"to\": 2069, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A tribute to Notre-Dame cathedral, in the process of being renovated after a devastating fire in 2019, is guaranteed, possibly with dancers on its scaffolding.\", \"from\": 2071, \"to\": 2230, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Starting at19:30(SA time), two thirds of the Paris Olympics 2024 opening ceremony will take place in daylight - the weather forecast shows cloudy skies and moderate temperatures - and will end with a light show.\", \"from\": 2232, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The music will be a mix of classical, traditional 'chanson francaise', as well as rap and electro.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2535, \"end\": 2542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_dance_music\", \"score\": 0.9999994004139786, \"rank\": 5.9362895646548e-07, \"text\": \"electro\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_dance_music\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Electronic_dance_music\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Franco-Malian R&B star Aya Nakamura is set to be one of the star performers despite criticism from far-right politicians, including Marine Le Pen, who suggested in March that an appearance by her would \\\"humiliate\\\" France.\", \"from\": 2545, \"to\": 2766, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2559, \"end\": 2562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhythm_and_blues\", \"score\": 0.9999999998935891, \"rank\": 1.0620175404262862e-10, \"text\": \"R&B\", \"types\": [\"Q188451\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhythm_and_blues\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rhythm_and_blues\"}, {\"begin\": 2568, \"end\": 2580, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aya Nakamura\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aya_Nakamura\"}, {\"begin\": 2677, \"end\": 2690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Le Pen\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Le_Pen\"}, {\"begin\": 2759, \"end\": 2765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999990541255, \"rank\": 5.668839206846921e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Lady Gaga and Celine Dion have both been spotted in Paris, fuelling rumours they will appear.\", \"from\": 2768, \"to\": 2861, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2768, \"end\": 2777, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}, {\"begin\": 2782, \"end\": 2793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.117387784167734e-53, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}, {\"begin\": 2820, \"end\": 2825, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.562606046249089e-21, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"French electro superstars Daft Punk have turned down an invitation to play, while globe-trotting French DJ David Guetta has been overlooked - much to his irritation.\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 3028, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2889, \"end\": 2898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daft_Punk\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.92852044318936e-17, \"text\": \"Daft Punk\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q215380\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daft_Punk\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daft_Punk\"}, {\"begin\": 2960, \"end\": 2966, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9944795295983407, \"rank\": 0.005125731490609682, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 2970, \"end\": 2982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Guetta\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Guetta\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Guetta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Guetta\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked to sum up his message last week, Jolly said it was \\\"love.\\\"\", \"from\": 3030, \"to\": 3094, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Despite the risk of irking conservatives, he said his work would be a celebration of cultural, linguistic, religious and sexual diversity in France and around the world.\", \"from\": 3096, \"to\": 3265, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3237, \"end\": 3243, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999990541255, \"rank\": 5.668839206846921e-10, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I think the people who want to live together in this diversity, this otherness, are much more numerous, but we make less noise,\\\" he told AFP.\", \"from\": 3267, \"to\": 3409, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3405, \"end\": 3408, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.914788629346157e-15, \"text\": \"AFP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It is fair to assume it will be nothing like the widely panned retro-styled opening ceremony of last year's rugby World Cup, which featured a succession of French cliches from baguettes to berets and the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 3411, \"to\": 3628, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3567, \"end\": 3573, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9944795295983407, \"rank\": 0.005125731490609682, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And do not expect a three-hour tribute to French greatness to rival the nationalistic pageantry seen at the Beijing Games in 2008.\", \"from\": 3630, \"to\": 3760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3672, \"end\": 3678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9944795295983407, \"rank\": 0.005125731490609682, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The opening ceremony in Beijing in 2008 was exactly what we did not want to do,\\\" Boucheron told Le Monde newspaper.\", \"from\": 3762, \"to\": 3878, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3787, \"end\": 3794, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"score\": 0.7868323653293798, \"rank\": 0.27091077730413726, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beijing\"}, {\"begin\": 3844, \"end\": 3853, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Boucheron\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boucheron\"}, {\"begin\": 3859, \"end\": 3867, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Monde\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Monde\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"With so much still under wraps, it's hard to predict.\", \"from\": 3880, \"to\": 3933, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The performance by Nakamura, after so much controversy about her role, will be a major moment so soon after parliamentary elections that saw the anti-immigration far-right gain a historic 143 seats in the national parliament.\", \"from\": 3935, \"to\": 4160, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly has strongly hinted that a submersible or submarine will emerge from the waters of the Seine at some point.\", \"from\": 4162, \"to\": 4275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4255, \"end\": 4260, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9634672690866536e-19, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The identity of the final torch holder who will light the Olympic cauldron in the gardens in front of the Louvre museum also remains unknown, although triple gold medal-winning sprinter Marie-Jose Perec is among the leading contenders.\", \"from\": 4277, \"to\": 4512, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4383, \"end\": 4389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"score\": 0.9845179223315753, \"rank\": 0.01572554172652347, \"text\": \"Louvre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\", \"Q33506\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Louvre\"}, {\"begin\": 4463, \"end\": 4479, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"score\": 0.9999999999290594, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marie-Jose Perec\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marie-Jos\\u00e9_P\\u00e9rec\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The biggest moment of all might simply be the end if everyone gets home safely.\", \"from\": 4514, \"to\": 4593, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The ceremony has given French police cold sweats ever since it was unveiled in 2021 because of the difficulty of securing so many people over such a vast urban area.\", \"from\": 4595, \"to\": 4760, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4618, \"end\": 4631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.4519276164438845e-39, \"text\": \"French police\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Law_enforcement_in_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"By Garrin Lambley \\u00a9 Agence France-Presse  WIN R2 000: Take The South African's SASSA Survey  The South African is hiring!\", \"from\": 4762, \"to\": 4883, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4772, \"end\": 4779, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lambley_railway_station\", \"score\": 0.999047327346806, \"rank\": 0.0009535811012283687, \"text\": \"Lambley\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lambley_railway_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lambley_railway_station\"}, {\"begin\": 4782, \"end\": 4802, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Agence France-Presse\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Agence_France-Presse\"}, {\"begin\": 4804, \"end\": 4807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"score\": 0.9999999857209333, \"rank\": 1.4125467453220047e-08, \"text\": \"WIN\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/WIN_Television\"}, {\"begin\": 4808, \"end\": 4810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"score\": 0.9999973070571166, \"rank\": 2.582553139971922e-06, \"text\": \"R2\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/DVD_region_code\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Freelance writing positions available  Follow The South African on Facebook for the latest local and international news  Follow The South African's Wh